      • internalCountModels

        protected BigInteger internalCountModels​(int thresh)
        Counts an epsilon-approximate estimate of the model count of the underlying formula, by partitioning the space of all the models into "small" cells containing at most pivot models.
        Specified by:
        internalCountModels in class AbstractApproxMC
        Parameters:
        thresh - The bound for the number of models in a cell.
        Returns:
        The estimate of the model count, or null to report a counting error, i.e;, when all generated cells were either empty or too big.

      • reset

        public void reset()
        Description copied from interface: IModelCounter
        Resets this counter. This method only makes sure that counting again the models will return the same results. In particular, none of the original constraints are removed.
